00:00:03.500 --> 00:00:05.000 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:09.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Thinking Allowed,
conversations on the leading

00:00:09.710 --> 00:00:14.120 align:middle line:84%
edge of knowledge and discovery
with psychologist Jeffrey

00:00:14.120 --> 00:00:15.207 align:middle line:90%
Mishlove.

00:00:15.207 --> 00:00:18.616 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:18.616 --> 00:00:31.280 align:middle line:90%


00:00:31.280 --> 00:00:32.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello and welcome.

00:00:32.220 --> 00:00:33.320 align:middle line:90%
I'm Jeffrey Mishlove.

00:00:33.320 --> 00:00:36.320 align:middle line:84%
Today we are
exploring once again

00:00:36.320 --> 00:00:39.620 align:middle line:84%
transforming our
relationship with the Earth.

00:00:39.620 --> 00:00:41.960 align:middle line:84%
My guest, Dr. Ralph
Metzner, is one

00:00:41.960 --> 00:00:47.570 align:middle line:84%
of the pioneers of the 21st
century consciousness movement.

00:00:47.570 --> 00:00:50.510 align:middle line:84%
He is co-author of "The
Psychedelic Experience"

00:00:50.510 --> 00:00:52.910 align:middle line:84%
and author of many
other books, including

00:00:52.910 --> 00:00:58.940 align:middle line:84%
"Maps of Consciousness," "The
Unfolding Self," "Ayahuasca,"

00:00:58.940 --> 00:01:01.370 align:middle line:90%
and "Green Psychology."

00:01:01.370 --> 00:01:04.730 align:middle line:84%
He is also president of
the Green Earth Foundation.

00:01:04.730 --> 00:01:05.690 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Ralph.

00:01:05.690 --> 00:01:06.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:11.300 align:middle line:84%
>> We have been talking about
the way in which we need

00:01:11.300 --> 00:01:15.680 align:middle line:84%
to come up with an entirely
new vision of who we are

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:18.090 align:middle line:84%
in relationship to
our environment.

00:01:18.090 --> 00:01:21.410 align:middle line:84%
That environmentalists seemed
to have learned by now that it's

00:01:21.410 --> 00:01:24.950 align:middle line:84%
not enough to tell people
that we must take care

00:01:24.950 --> 00:01:28.420 align:middle line:84%
of the environment, that we must
be good, that we must recycle,

00:01:28.420 --> 00:01:31.100 align:middle line:84%
that those kinds of
moralistic admonitions

00:01:31.100 --> 00:01:32.590 align:middle line:90%
are not going to do the job.

00:01:32.590 --> 00:01:36.910 align:middle line:84%
We have to understand
in our bones

00:01:36.910 --> 00:01:38.480 align:middle line:90%
our connection with the Earth.

00:01:38.480 --> 00:01:40.880 align:middle line:84%
And one of the points
that you have raised

00:01:40.880 --> 00:01:44.420 align:middle line:84%
is that a great
deal of wisdom can

00:01:44.420 --> 00:01:48.660 align:middle line:84%
be gathered by looking at the
esoteric cultures of humanity.

00:01:48.660 --> 00:01:52.820 align:middle line:84%
They seem to have preserved
a sense of our connection.

00:01:52.820 --> 00:01:56.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Right, the esoteric and the
Eastern and the Indigenous.

00:01:56.660 --> 00:02:01.880 align:middle line:84%
For example, in the Middle Ages,
the medieval times, in Europe

00:02:01.880 --> 00:02:05.000 align:middle line:84%
there existed this tradition
of alchemy, which in a way

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:07.790 align:middle line:84%
can be seen as being
parallel to what was called

00:02:07.790 --> 00:02:11.080 align:middle line:90%
yoga in India and shamanism.

00:02:11.080 --> 00:02:15.230 align:middle line:84%
I like to think of alchemy,
yoga, and shamanism

00:02:15.230 --> 00:02:22.250 align:middle line:84%
as the three major systems of
consciousness transformation.

00:02:22.250 --> 00:02:25.400 align:middle line:84%
Yoga more in the East, and
alchemy more in the West,

00:02:25.400 --> 00:02:27.740 align:middle line:84%
and shamanism really
being the original one

00:02:27.740 --> 00:02:29.490 align:middle line:90%
that they grew out of.

00:02:29.490 --> 00:02:33.563 align:middle line:84%
Alchemy seems to have grown out
of the shamanism of the miners

00:02:33.563 --> 00:02:35.480 align:middle line:84%
and the metal workers
that went into the Earth

00:02:35.480 --> 00:02:38.060 align:middle line:84%
and extracted the
metal from the Earth.

00:02:38.060 --> 00:02:42.140 align:middle line:84%
And they had a very almost
kind of a mystical and very

00:02:42.140 --> 00:02:46.430 align:middle line:84%
organic psychic kind
of spiritual feeling

00:02:46.430 --> 00:02:47.690 align:middle line:90%
for what they were doing.

00:02:47.690 --> 00:02:48.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Now, you're not referring--

00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:49.708 align:middle line:90%
>> The miners, the metalists.

00:02:49.708 --> 00:02:53.810 align:middle line:84%
>> --simply to the idea that
we can convert lead into gold.

00:02:53.810 --> 00:02:57.770 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the idea that
can be seen as a metaphor.

00:02:57.770 --> 00:02:59.810 align:middle line:84%
Psychological alchemy
would say it's a metaphor.

00:02:59.810 --> 00:03:01.670 align:middle line:84%
Now, there were also
the material aspect

00:03:01.670 --> 00:03:04.290 align:middle line:84%
of alchemy, which led to
what we call chemistry.

00:03:04.290 --> 00:03:07.580 align:middle line:84%
But in the 15th, 16th
century, those two aspects

00:03:07.580 --> 00:03:10.890 align:middle line:84%
split apart, just like astrology
and astronomy split apart.

00:03:10.890 --> 00:03:14.270 align:middle line:84%
Because they used to be one
science, where everything

00:03:14.270 --> 00:03:16.280 align:middle line:90%
was seen as interrelationship.

00:03:16.280 --> 00:03:18.410 align:middle line:84%
But then with the
rise of science

00:03:18.410 --> 00:03:21.480 align:middle line:84%
and the rise of a causal
deterministic view, science

00:03:21.480 --> 00:03:23.460 align:middle line:84%
says, well, we don't
want to have anything

00:03:23.460 --> 00:03:26.690 align:middle line:84%
to do with astrology
and alchemy.

00:03:26.690 --> 00:03:29.090 align:middle line:84%
We want to be just
strictly scientific.

00:03:29.090 --> 00:03:31.730 align:middle line:84%
Even although the founding
fathers were not like that.

00:03:31.730 --> 00:03:34.118 align:middle line:84%
And many people don't realize
that Newton, Isaac Newton,

00:03:34.118 --> 00:03:36.410 align:middle line:84%
the founding father of modern
science, was an alchemist

00:03:36.410 --> 00:03:38.750 align:middle line:84%
and did alchemical
studies for 20 years.

00:03:38.750 --> 00:03:40.283 align:middle line:84%
And Johannes Kepler,
who discovered

00:03:40.283 --> 00:03:42.200 align:middle line:84%
the laws of planetary
motion was an astrologer

00:03:42.200 --> 00:03:44.570 align:middle line:84%
who used to set up
horoscopes for people.

00:03:44.570 --> 00:03:47.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, as I understand,
these I'll call them esoteric

00:03:47.990 --> 00:03:52.310 align:middle line:84%
sciences, they're predicated
on the idea that the scientist

00:03:52.310 --> 00:03:55.730 align:middle line:84%
must transform
herself or himself.

00:03:55.730 --> 00:04:01.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, it's that we live in a
universe of interrelationships.

00:04:01.010 --> 00:04:02.690 align:middle line:84%
It's in a way much
closer to what

00:04:02.690 --> 00:04:06.993 align:middle line:84%
we, in postmodern thinking,
call a systems view,

00:04:06.993 --> 00:04:07.910 align:middle line:90%
a living systems view.

00:04:07.910 --> 00:04:11.510 align:middle line:84%
That the universe-- alchemists
and hermetic teachings

00:04:11.510 --> 00:04:14.510 align:middle line:84%
talked a lot about this
notion of correspondence.

00:04:14.510 --> 00:04:16.010 align:middle line:84%
There's a correspondence,
they said,

00:04:16.010 --> 00:04:18.260 align:middle line:84%
between the macrocosm
and the microcosm.

00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:22.640 align:middle line:84%
That the basic principles are
the same at all these levels

00:04:22.640 --> 00:04:23.870 align:middle line:90%
of interrelationship.

00:04:23.870 --> 00:04:25.520 align:middle line:90%
That's what systems theory says.

00:04:25.520 --> 00:04:30.950 align:middle line:84%
Systems theory says you look at
the world as systems existing

00:04:30.950 --> 00:04:33.710 align:middle line:84%
at many levels of
wholes and parts,

00:04:33.710 --> 00:04:36.200 align:middle line:84%
and what are the
common patterns?

00:04:36.200 --> 00:04:38.930 align:middle line:84%
And everything is
really a network,

00:04:38.930 --> 00:04:40.910 align:middle line:90%
a web of interconnectedness.

00:04:40.910 --> 00:04:42.120 align:middle line:90%
That's the systems view.

00:04:42.120 --> 00:04:46.250 align:middle line:84%
That's not very far from
what the hermetic teachings

00:04:46.250 --> 00:04:49.790 align:middle line:84%
and the mystical teachings
said, this principle

00:04:49.790 --> 00:04:51.050 align:middle line:90%
of correspondence.

00:04:51.050 --> 00:04:56.360 align:middle line:84%
And so the alchemists
used the language.

00:04:56.360 --> 00:04:59.120 align:middle line:84%
You could say the psychological
or philosophical alchemists

00:04:59.120 --> 00:05:02.600 align:middle line:84%
used the language of
chemistry or metallurgy

00:05:02.600 --> 00:05:05.360 align:middle line:84%
to describe
psychological processes.

00:05:05.360 --> 00:05:07.640 align:middle line:84%
So transformation
of lead into gold

00:05:07.640 --> 00:05:11.910 align:middle line:84%
was the quest to transform, say,
leaden states of consciousness,

00:05:11.910 --> 00:05:13.730 align:middle line:84%
which would be like
depression, darkness,

00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:18.290 align:middle line:84%
heaviness, to
listlessness, no energy,

00:05:18.290 --> 00:05:22.610 align:middle line:84%
saturnine, melancholy, to gold
kind of consciousness, which

00:05:22.610 --> 00:05:25.660 align:middle line:84%
would be reflective,
shining, enlightened.

00:05:25.660 --> 00:05:27.420 align:middle line:90%
It's kind of like enlightenment.

00:05:27.420 --> 00:05:28.970 align:middle line:90%
So it's symbolic.

00:05:28.970 --> 00:05:31.490 align:middle line:84%
So it was not either
one or the other.

00:05:31.490 --> 00:05:34.430 align:middle line:84%
It was both, just like
astrology was both.

00:05:34.430 --> 00:05:38.110 align:middle line:84%
Astrology as a system of
looking at the correspondences

00:05:38.110 --> 00:05:41.810 align:middle line:84%
is based on accurately measuring
the positions of the planets

00:05:41.810 --> 00:05:43.980 align:middle line:84%
and looking at the
relationships between them.

00:05:43.980 --> 00:05:46.010 align:middle line:84%
But in addition, then,
it looks at, well,

00:05:46.010 --> 00:05:49.160 align:middle line:84%
what are the harmonic
correspondences?

00:05:49.160 --> 00:05:50.863 align:middle line:90%
Not so much causal effects.

00:05:50.863 --> 00:05:52.280 align:middle line:84%
Not that they're
saying that there

00:05:52.280 --> 00:05:54.050 align:middle line:84%
are rays coming on
the planets that

00:05:54.050 --> 00:05:56.000 align:middle line:84%
cause you to think
in a certain way.

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:58.610 align:middle line:84%
But we live in this network
of interrelationships

00:05:58.610 --> 00:06:01.460 align:middle line:84%
that are patterned and have
patterned similarities.

00:06:01.460 --> 00:06:04.470 align:middle line:90%
So it's very interesting to me.

00:06:04.470 --> 00:06:08.030 align:middle line:84%
And I've gone, like Jung, who
was really a modern alchemist

00:06:08.030 --> 00:06:09.950 align:middle line:84%
and wrote several
books on alchemy

00:06:09.950 --> 00:06:11.060 align:middle line:90%
to study that symbolism.

00:06:11.060 --> 00:06:11.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Carl Jung.

00:06:11.860 --> 00:06:14.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Carl Jung, yeah, has many
implications and applications

00:06:14.840 --> 00:06:18.460 align:middle line:84%
in psychotherapy because they
mapped out these processes

00:06:18.460 --> 00:06:19.940 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness transformation.

00:06:19.940 --> 00:06:21.950 align:middle line:84%
It's all transformation
of the elements.

00:06:21.950 --> 00:06:24.930 align:middle line:84%
The elements relate to what
the psychological functions--

00:06:24.930 --> 00:06:27.470 align:middle line:84%
earth, air, fire, and water
relate to thinking, intuition,

00:06:27.470 --> 00:06:29.130 align:middle line:90%
feeling, and sensation.

00:06:29.130 --> 00:06:31.580 align:middle line:84%
So you when you're doing
psychotherapy or involved

00:06:31.580 --> 00:06:34.470 align:middle line:84%
in any transformation
process, you're

00:06:34.470 --> 00:06:35.720 align:middle line:90%
changing your way of thinking.

00:06:35.720 --> 00:06:36.890 align:middle line:84%
You're changing
the way you feel.

00:06:36.890 --> 00:06:39.320 align:middle line:84%
You're changing the way you look
at your world, the perception.

00:06:39.320 --> 00:06:40.990 align:middle line:84%
And you're changing
the physical body,

00:06:40.990 --> 00:06:42.840 align:middle line:90%
so it has healing implications.

00:06:42.840 --> 00:06:45.170 align:middle line:84%
The medieval really
gifted healers,

00:06:45.170 --> 00:06:49.040 align:middle line:84%
there's a whole medical system
based on alchemy and the system

00:06:49.040 --> 00:06:51.950 align:middle line:90%
of the humours and so forth.

00:06:51.950 --> 00:06:54.200 align:middle line:84%
And the alchemists, one
of the core principles

00:06:54.200 --> 00:06:56.240 align:middle line:90%
was that you follow nature.

00:06:56.240 --> 00:06:58.340 align:middle line:84%
You have that
attitude of humility.

00:06:58.340 --> 00:06:59.190 align:middle line:90%
Very different.

00:06:59.190 --> 00:07:02.820 align:middle line:84%
See, it was an
underground tradition.

00:07:02.820 --> 00:07:06.950 align:middle line:84%
It was underground in
relationship to the church too.

00:07:06.950 --> 00:07:09.950 align:middle line:84%
Because the church
felt that it wanted

00:07:09.950 --> 00:07:13.520 align:middle line:84%
to be the sole arbiter, the
sole source of knowledge

00:07:13.520 --> 00:07:17.210 align:middle line:84%
and certainty and what was
valuable and what was ideal.

00:07:17.210 --> 00:07:20.450 align:middle line:84%
It didn't really want people
to be doing transformation

00:07:20.450 --> 00:07:22.022 align:middle line:90%
on their own.

00:07:22.022 --> 00:07:23.480 align:middle line:84%
It's a spiritual
tradition, meaning

00:07:23.480 --> 00:07:25.987 align:middle line:84%
that you get in touch with
your own spirit within.

00:07:25.987 --> 00:07:27.570 align:middle line:84%
So they disguised
everything that they

00:07:27.570 --> 00:07:31.070 align:middle line:84%
did in this elaborate
symbolic code, which

00:07:31.070 --> 00:07:33.590 align:middle line:84%
makes it almost
incomprehensible unless you

00:07:33.590 --> 00:07:35.840 align:middle line:84%
take the trouble to
kind of go into it.

00:07:35.840 --> 00:07:41.292 align:middle line:84%
And so the same idea that
the shamans and the animistic

00:07:41.292 --> 00:07:43.250 align:middle line:84%
and [INAUDIBLE] people
have, you follow nature.

00:07:43.250 --> 00:07:46.830 align:middle line:84%
It puts you in a humble
position, rather than

00:07:46.830 --> 00:07:50.210 align:middle line:84%
just dominator position that
we're superior and we know best

00:07:50.210 --> 00:07:54.540 align:middle line:84%
and we can manage, which
even some people might say,

00:07:54.540 --> 00:07:57.080 align:middle line:84%
well, OK, we don't
want to have dominion,

00:07:57.080 --> 00:07:59.900 align:middle line:84%
but we want to be
enlightened stewards.

00:07:59.900 --> 00:08:01.850 align:middle line:84%
So even the notion
of stewardship,

00:08:01.850 --> 00:08:05.230 align:middle line:84%
while it's suddenly better
than, say, dominating,

00:08:05.230 --> 00:08:07.280 align:middle line:84%
still has this notion
of superiority.

00:08:07.280 --> 00:08:10.370 align:middle line:84%
And it says that,
well, we somehow

00:08:10.370 --> 00:08:12.920 align:middle line:90%
know enough to be stewards.

00:08:12.920 --> 00:08:14.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:08:14.110 --> 00:08:16.340 align:middle line:84%
>> As I say, it's
better than nothing.

00:08:16.340 --> 00:08:18.860 align:middle line:84%
And it's better to
be a wise steward.

00:08:18.860 --> 00:08:23.530 align:middle line:84%
And so that's definitely
one thing to be encouraged.

00:08:23.530 --> 00:08:26.360 align:middle line:84%
And again, I'm talking
in generalities.

00:08:26.360 --> 00:08:29.060 align:middle line:84%
There have always been
individual scientists.

00:08:29.060 --> 00:08:31.370 align:middle line:84%
There have always been
also individual Christians

00:08:31.370 --> 00:08:33.578 align:middle line:84%
in the different traditions
who have had a completely

00:08:33.578 --> 00:08:35.344 align:middle line:90%
different attitude.

00:08:35.344 --> 00:08:38.184 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we have, in our
culture, the notion--

00:08:38.184 --> 00:08:43.730 align:middle line:84%
well, for example, we can
exterminate insects or pests,

00:08:43.730 --> 00:08:45.530 align:middle line:90%
spiders, for examples.

00:08:45.530 --> 00:08:49.520 align:middle line:84%
Indigenous people revered
spiders and snakes

00:08:49.520 --> 00:08:50.570 align:middle line:90%
and bats and toads--

00:08:50.570 --> 00:08:51.410 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:08:51.410 --> 00:08:54.410 align:middle line:84%
>> Creatures that we might think
of as beneath our contempt.

00:08:54.410 --> 00:08:57.590 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, we think of them
as pests or vermin to be

00:08:57.590 --> 00:08:58.670 align:middle line:90%
exterminated.

00:08:58.670 --> 00:09:02.660 align:middle line:84%
I myself, just in the
last couple of years,

00:09:02.660 --> 00:09:05.810 align:middle line:84%
have had a major change of
consciousness in relationship

00:09:05.810 --> 00:09:09.050 align:middle line:84%
to insects, although I've
worked with shamanistic ideas

00:09:09.050 --> 00:09:12.080 align:middle line:84%
and respecting animals and
animal spirits for a long time.

00:09:12.080 --> 00:09:14.300 align:middle line:84%
But I still had the
common assumption,

00:09:14.300 --> 00:09:16.290 align:middle line:84%
unexamined assumption
in my mind that insects

00:09:16.290 --> 00:09:20.332 align:middle line:84%
were sort of below consideration
and could be avoided.

00:09:20.332 --> 00:09:22.040 align:middle line:84%
And I read this
wonderful book by a woman

00:09:22.040 --> 00:09:24.410 align:middle line:84%
called Joanne Lauck called
"The Voice of the Infinite

00:09:24.410 --> 00:09:26.750 align:middle line:84%
in the Small," which
is about rethinking

00:09:26.750 --> 00:09:29.240 align:middle line:90%
the human-insect consideration.

00:09:29.240 --> 00:09:31.730 align:middle line:90%
I'll just tell you one example.

00:09:31.730 --> 00:09:32.780 align:middle line:90%
We used to have ants.

00:09:32.780 --> 00:09:35.120 align:middle line:84%
Ants would come
in in the kitchen,

00:09:35.120 --> 00:09:37.220 align:middle line:84%
and we'd wipe them
up and take a sponge

00:09:37.220 --> 00:09:39.440 align:middle line:90%
and just kill a couple of them.

00:09:39.440 --> 00:09:40.588 align:middle line:90%
Just wipe.

00:09:40.588 --> 00:09:41.630 align:middle line:90%
Oh, they were a nuisance.

00:09:41.630 --> 00:09:42.530 align:middle line:90%
They were disgusting.

00:09:42.530 --> 00:09:44.840 align:middle line:84%
They were dirty, and
they carry diseases.

00:09:44.840 --> 00:09:48.060 align:middle line:84%
All kind of assumptions,
but no real reason for it.

00:09:48.060 --> 00:09:49.560 align:middle line:84%
So I stopped and
thought about it.

00:09:49.560 --> 00:09:51.380 align:middle line:84%
Wait a minute, what
are these doing here?

00:09:51.380 --> 00:09:54.110 align:middle line:90%
These are ants.

00:09:54.110 --> 00:09:55.650 align:middle line:90%
They're looking for food.

00:09:55.650 --> 00:09:58.032 align:middle line:90%
Now, I can respect that.

00:09:58.032 --> 00:09:59.990 align:middle line:84%
In fact, they're very
good at looking for food.

00:09:59.990 --> 00:10:01.657 align:middle line:84%
They're coming in
from outside the house

00:10:01.657 --> 00:10:03.140 align:middle line:84%
and coming in
where there's food.

00:10:03.140 --> 00:10:04.640 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
they're looking for.

00:10:04.640 --> 00:10:06.710 align:middle line:90%
So I talked to them.

00:10:06.710 --> 00:10:10.010 align:middle line:84%
And I asked my wife and
the rest of my family

00:10:10.010 --> 00:10:12.530 align:middle line:84%
also to talk to them because
it wouldn't do for one person

00:10:12.530 --> 00:10:14.690 align:middle line:84%
to have a different attitude
and the other person

00:10:14.690 --> 00:10:17.390 align:middle line:84%
in the family just to
kill and get rid of them.

00:10:17.390 --> 00:10:19.640 align:middle line:84%
So I talked to them, and I
put out some food for them.

00:10:19.640 --> 00:10:22.455 align:middle line:84%
And I said, OK,
you can have this.

00:10:22.455 --> 00:10:25.100 align:middle line:84%
I gave them a big cookie,
a piece of cookie,

00:10:25.100 --> 00:10:26.780 align:middle line:90%
and said you can have that.

00:10:26.780 --> 00:10:29.240 align:middle line:90%
And then would you please--

00:10:29.240 --> 00:10:32.240 align:middle line:84%
I really admire you, and I like
that you are looking for food.

00:10:32.240 --> 00:10:33.150 align:middle line:90%
I can relate to that.

00:10:33.150 --> 00:10:34.430 align:middle line:90%
I can have empathy for that.

00:10:34.430 --> 00:10:35.513 align:middle line:90%
Because that's what we do.

00:10:35.513 --> 00:10:37.060 align:middle line:90%
We're all searching for food.

00:10:37.060 --> 00:10:38.810 align:middle line:84%
And you can have that
food, and then would

00:10:38.810 --> 00:10:41.120 align:middle line:90%
you leave the kitchen, please?

00:10:41.120 --> 00:10:43.370 align:middle line:84%
So I went, and I walked away,
and two hours later they

00:10:43.370 --> 00:10:44.170 align:middle line:90%
were gone.

00:10:44.170 --> 00:10:45.920 align:middle line:84%
And they had
cleaned the counter.

00:10:45.920 --> 00:10:47.503 align:middle line:84%
They had actually
cleaned the counter.

00:10:47.503 --> 00:10:50.410 align:middle line:84%
Of course, they took all the
food and cleaned the counter.

00:10:50.410 --> 00:10:51.777 align:middle line:90%
My wife was impressed.

00:10:51.777 --> 00:10:52.610 align:middle line:90%
And we did it again.

00:10:52.610 --> 00:10:53.652 align:middle line:90%
I tried it several times.

00:10:53.652 --> 00:10:55.190 align:middle line:90%
It worked, systematically.

00:10:55.190 --> 00:10:58.220 align:middle line:84%
We've never been
bothered by ants since.

00:10:58.220 --> 00:11:00.140 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't dream
of spraying them.

00:11:00.140 --> 00:11:03.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, this is a very
interesting testimony

00:11:03.110 --> 00:11:06.080 align:middle line:84%
to the possibilities of
a whole different kind

00:11:06.080 --> 00:11:06.880 align:middle line:90%
of relationship--

00:11:06.880 --> 00:11:07.680 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:11:07.680 --> 00:11:09.470 align:middle line:84%
